					<p>I&#8217;m fighting the 250-word limit every topic, I&#8217;d be very happy to try something a bit longer. I seem to top out naturally at about 350 and it&#8217;s a struggle to get it down to the limit. (I failed dismally last time, it was around 280, and for &#8220;Spanner&#8221; I&#8217;m going to have to scrap what I&#8217;ve written and do something completely different, I simply cannot get it below about 320). Nantalith&#8217;s drabble idea fills me with horror and dread and a creeping sense of loss.</p>
