				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I think I&#8217;ll always have a word limit problem ;&gt;. But the more we do this, the more I try to be layered with the stuff that I&#8217;m writing, and 250 is rather limiting to complexity unless one is fiendishly cunning, which I find I can&#8217;t be every submission in a row. Most of my submissions for this have settled naturally into about 300-350 words, and have had to be ruthlessly pruned to get them any smaller.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m with Nantalith on word options. Maybe we should have three possible lengths (250, 350, 500? or 100, 250, 350?), and either specify a length for each topic, or start asking people to include the word limit they&#8217;re working to with each submission.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

